rojects wikimedia commons languages deutschespañolفارسیfrançaislëtzebuergeschpolskiрусскийsimple englishاردو edit links this page was last edited on  july  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view william wrigley jr  wikipedia william wrigley jr from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from william wrigley jr jump to navigation search for other people by this name see william wrigley william l wrigley jr born september   philadelphia pennsylvania united states died january   aged  phoenix arizona united states resting place forest lawn memorial park glendale california occupation confectionery magnate net worth usd  million at the time of his death approximately th of us gnp spouses ada elizabeth foote children dorothy philip knight wrigley parents william and mary a ladley signature william l wrigley jr september   – january   was an american chewing gum industrialist he was founder and eponym of the wm wrigley jr company in  he was born in philadelphia pennsylvania wrigley jr is rumored to have cofounded his namesake company with a lesserknown canadian named m bessemer who was a close childhood friend of wrigley jr contents  life  death  gallery  see also  references  external links lifeedit wrigley was born on september   during the civil war in philadelphia in  at the age of  wrigley moved from philadelphia to chicago he had  to his name and with it he formed a business to sell wrigleys scouring soap he offered customers small premiums particularly baking powder as an incentive to buy his soap finding the baking powder was more popular than his soap wrigley switched to selling baking powder and giving his customers two packages of chewing gum for each can of baking powder they purchased again wrigley found that the premium he offered was more popular than his base product and his company began to concentrate on the manufacture and sale of chewing gum in this business wrigley made his name and fortune wrigley played an instrumental role in the development of santa catalina island california off the shore of los angeles california he bought a controlling interest in the santa catalina island company in  and with the company received the island wrigley improved the island with public utilities new steamships a hotel the casino building and extensive plantings of trees shrubs and flowers he also sought to create an enterprise that would help employ local residents by making use of clay and minerals found on the island at a beach near avalon in  william wrigley jr created the pebbly beach quarry and tile plant along with creating jobs for avalon residents the plant also supplied material for wrigleys numerous building projects on the island after the building of avalons casino see avalon theater catalina in  the catalina clay products tile and pottery plant began producing glazed tiles dinnerware and other household items such as bookends another of wrigleys legacies was his plan for the future of catalina island—that it be protected for future generations to enjoy in  his son philip k wrigley established the catalina island conservancy for this purpose and transferred all family ownership to it wrigley is honored by the wrigley memorial in the wrigley botanical gardens on the island in  wrigley bought a minority stake in the chicago cubs baseball team as part of a group headed by charles weeghman former owner of the federal leagues chicago whales over the next four years as weeghmans lunchcounter business declined he was forced to sell much of his stock in the ball club to wrigley by  weeghman had sold all of his stock to wrigley making wrigley the largest shareholder and principal owner and by  wrigley was majority owner wrigley field the cubs ballpark in chicago is named for him the nowdemolished former home of the los angeles angels of the pacific coast league at that time the cubs top farm team was also called wrigley field wrigley purchased the chicago cubs from albert lasker in  the arizona biltmore hotel in phoenix arizona was partially financed and wholly owned by wrigley who finished the nearby wrigley mansion as a winter cottage in  at  square feet  m it was the smallest of his five residences deathedit william wrigley jr died on january   at his phoenix arizona mansion at age  and was interred in his customdesigned sarcophagus located in the tower of the wrigley memorial  botanical gardens near his beloved home on californias catalina island in  wrigleys remains were moved to allow the gardens to be made public there is a rumor that the remains were moved during world war ii due to wartime security concerns his original grave memorial marker still adorns the tower site wrigley was reinterred in the corridor alcove end of the sanctuary of gratitude at forest lawn memorial park cemetery in glendale california he left his fortune to daughter dorothy wrigley offield and son philip k wrigley the son continued to run the company until his death in  his ashes were interred near his father in the same sanctuary of gratitude alcove his greatgrandson william wrigley jr ii is the executive chairman and former ceo of the wrigley company wrigley was inducted into the junior achievement us business hall of fame in  galleryedit william wrigley jr william wrigley jr on the cover of time in   the wrigley mansion in phoenix arizona was built between  and  it is located at  east telewa trail the historic mansion is also known as “la colina solana” the mansion has been designated as a phoenix point of pride the mansion was listed as the “william wrigley jr winter cottage” on the national register of historic places on august   ref   the former wrigley mansion in pasadena california  wrigleys steamship the catalina leaving the los angeles docks   the wrigley lofts formerly wm wrigley jr co ltd located in toronto canada  see alsoedit tournament house formerly the wrigley mansion in pasadena california referencesedit  klepper michael gunther michael  the wealthy  from benjamin franklin to bill gates—a ranking of the richest americans past and present secaucus new jersey carol publishing group p xiii isbn  oclc    wrigley exhibit opens at the catalina island museum tonight catalina museum website   catalina pottery old and sold antiques auction  marketplace  sampler tour of art tiles from catalina island  httpwwwmsuedudaggycopbkofdeadobitswohtm  nancy wride a catalina oasis offers the mortal and the vital the los angeles times june   external linksedit biography resource center jack bales “weeghman and wrigley wrigleyivycom jack bales “wrigley jr and veeck sr” wrigleyivycom william wrigley jr at find a grave v t e chicago cubs formerly the chicago white stockings chicago colts and the chicago orphans based in chicago illinois franchise history seasons awards records nohitters players managers owners and executives broadcasters opening day starting pitchers firstround draft picks ballparks rd street grounds lakefront park west side park i south side park west side park ii wrigley field renovations spring training whittington park plant field rendezvous park blair field hohokam park sloan park lore curse of the billy goat babe ruths called shot steve bartman incident gatorade glove play homer in the gloamin the sandberg game fall of   home run chase brock for broglio merkles boner worst to first monday saves the american flag college of coaches excubs factor ken hubbs billy jurges incident game  culture tinker to evers to chance bleacher bums wrigley rooftops wrigleyville wayne messmer ronnie woo woo yosh kawano mike royko harry caray holy cow grant deporter wrigley company wrigley field ivy hey hey holy mackerel bill holden the hec